{"title_page": "Timethai", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=June 2012}}\n{{Infobox musical artist \n| name           = Dharmthai Plangsilp\n| image          = Timethai 1.jpg\n| caption        =\n| background     = solo_singer\n| birth_name     = Dharmthai Plangsilp\n| alias          = Timethai\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1996|1|02}}\n| origin         = {{flagicon|Thailand}} [[Bangkok]], Thailand\n| genre = Pop and [[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]\n| occupation     = Singer\n| years_active   = 2011&ndash;present\n| label           =\u0e01\u0e32\u0e21\u0e34\u0e01\u0e32\u0e40\u0e0a\u0e48 [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]] \u0e40\u0e22\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e34\u0e27\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e01 [[Yes!Music]]\n| website        = https://www.facebook.com/timethaiofficialpage\n}}\n\n'''Dharmthai Plangsilp''' ({{lang-th|\u0e18\u0e32\u0e21\u0e44\u0e17 \u0e41\u0e1e\u0e25\u0e07\u0e28\u0e34\u0e25\u0e1b\u0e4c}} - {{IPA-th|t\u02b0\u0251\u02d0mt\u02b0a\u026a p\u02b0l\u00e6\u014bs\u026an}}) (born January 2, 1996), known professionally as '''Timethai''' ({{IPA-th|t\u02b0\u0251\u02d0mt\u02b0a\u026a}}), is a Thai singer, songwriter, and dancer.  Timethai was discovered in 2010 when [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]]'s casting staff came across Timethai's Youtube videos which have been uploaded by a channel named 'Dharmthai'.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/user/dharmthai Dharmthai channel on Youtube ]</ref>  Timethai's dancing and choreography skills, cultivated since he was 7 years old, which couple uniquely with his ability to play traditional Thai instruments such as the Thai alto xylophone, Thai alto bamboo xylophone and Kong Wong ({{lang-th|\u0e06\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e27\u0e07}}),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UaV2WHeKQYo &#91;Scoop&#93; Timethai Timeline]</ref> captured the attention of the casting staff, who offered Timethai a one-year singing and dancing training opportunity, and soon signed him to their label [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]] under RS PLC. He graduated with a bachelor's degree from Srinakarinwirot University.\n\nTimethai's debut single, \"No More\", featuring Tomo and his unique hip-hop dancing style, was released in December 2011.  The music video \"No More\"<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N__KiLe4vhQ No More music video]</ref> reached more than 10,000,000 views on Youtube within just 5 months<ref>[http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1039 \u201c\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e25\u0e30 (No More)\u201d \u0e41\u0e23\u0e07\u0e17\u0e30\u0e25\u0e38 10,000,000 view \u0e41\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32!! ] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006074009/http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1039 |date=2012-10-06 }}</ref> and have been discussed nationwide.  Timethai followed up the release of his debut single with his second single \"The End\"<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=viD2tvNzhdQ The End music video]</ref> in April 2012. One month after its release, \"The End\" charted at number one in Thailand.<ref>[http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1027 Timethai \u0e41\u0e23\u0e07\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e22\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07 \u201c..\u0e08\u0e1a\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22 (The End)\u201d \u0e1e\u0e38\u0e48\u0e07\u0e02\u0e36\u0e49\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e48\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e15\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e19\u0e14\u0e31\u0e1a 1 \u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006104655/http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1027 |date=2012-10-06 }}</ref> Timethai is considered to be a rising newcomer in Thailand's music industry as well as Thailand's most popular young solo male artist.\n\n==Singles==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Singles\n!Album\n|-\n| rowspan = \"1\"|2011\n|No More (\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e25\u0e30) Feat. Tomo [[K-Otic]] \n| rowspan = \"4\"|TIMETHAI \n|-\n| rowspan = \"3\"|2012\n|The End (\u0e08\u0e1a\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22)\n|-\n|Top Secret (\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e30\u0e44\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e25\u0e37\u0e21\u0e1a\u0e2d\u0e01)\n|-\n|Always Da One (\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d) \n|-\n| rowspan = \"4\"|2013\n|In Time (\u0e21\u0e32\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e08\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e30) \n| rowspan = \"5\"|DRIFE \n|-\n|Blame It On Me (\u0e40\u0e08\u0e47\u0e1a\u0e04\u0e19\u0e40\u0e14\u0e35\u0e22\u0e27\u0e01\u0e47\u0e1e\u0e2d)\n|-\n|Spy (\u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e19\u0e18\u0e38\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e49\u0e2d)\n|-\n|All l Need (\u0e41\u0e04\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d)\n|-\n| rowspan = \"1\"|2014\n|Hidden Line (\u0e0a\u0e39\u0e49\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e44\u0e25\u0e19\u0e4c) Feat. \u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e41\u0e15 \u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e2a\u0e22\u0e32\u0e21\n|-\n| rowspan = \"1\"|2017\n|Don't Judge Me\n|-\n| rowspan = \"2\"|2018\n|Feelin with Twopee Southside and Notep\n|-\n|It's Time Feat. \u0e2b\u0e27\u0e32\u0e22\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2019\n|Impossible\n|-\n|Never Know \n|-\n|IDONTMIND \n|-\n|Muay Rong (\u0e21\u0e27\u0e22\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e07) ft.YOUNGGU,FIIXD,DAWUT, CD GUNTEE\n|-\n|WHATEVER (\u0e1e\u0e39\u0e14\u0e2d\u0e30\u0e44\u0e23\u0e01\u0e47\u0e40\u0e0a\u0e34\u0e0d)\n|-\n|Who Are you? (\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e15\u0e23\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e01)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2020\n| Thaitiana ft. Dennis Thaikoon,TAKA,KK\n|-\n|RnB\n|-\n|Sofa ft. NAP THE KID\n|-\n|When? (\u0e40\u0e21\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e44\u0e2b\u0e23\u0e48)\n|-\n|I Thought I Loved her (\u0e2a\u0e33\u0e04\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27\u0e1c\u0e34\u0e14) ft. DIAMOND MQT\n|-HipHop\n\n\n|}\n\n== Studio albums==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" width=\"250px\"|Album details\n!align=\"left\" width=\"300px\"|Track listing\n|-\n| align = \"left\"|''' TIMETHAI ''' \n* Released: 2012\n* Label: [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]]\n* Formats: Mini Album\n| \n#  No More (\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e25\u0e30)\n#  The End (\u0e08\u0e1a\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22)\n#  Top Secret (\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e30\u0e44\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e25\u0e37\u0e21\u0e1a\u0e2d\u0e01)\n#  Always Da One (\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d)\n|-\n| align = \"left\"|''' DRIFE ''' \n* Released: 2013\n* Label: [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]]\n* Formats: -\n| \n#  In Time (\u0e21\u0e32\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e08\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e30)\n#  Blame It On Me (\u0e40\u0e08\u0e47\u0e1a\u0e04\u0e19\u0e40\u0e14\u0e35\u0e22\u0e27\u0e01\u0e47\u0e1e\u0e2d)\n#  Spy (\u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e19\u0e18\u0e38\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e49\u0e2d)\n#  All l Need (\u0e41\u0e04\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d)\n|}\n\n== Concerts ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" width=\"400px\"|Title\n!align=\"left\" width=\"200px\"|Date\n!align=\"left\" width=\"250px\"|Venue\n|-\n| align = \"left\"|'''Biscuit Gap presents FFK AHOLIC CONCERT ''' ''(Guest)'' <ref>[http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/945 \u0e41\u0e16\u0e25\u0e07\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e13\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e21\u0e31\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e23\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e0d\u0e48\u0e08\u0e32\u0e01 KAMIKAZE Biscuit Gap Presents FFKAHOLIC CONCERT\u201d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120508170752/http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/945 |date=2012-05-08 }}</ref>\n| \nMay 26, 2012\n|\nRoyal Paragon Hall, Siam Paragon, Bangkok\n|-\n| align = \"left\"|'''KAMIKAZE THE 5th DESTINY CONCERT '''\n| \nOctober 13, 2012\n|\nRoyal Paragon Hall, Siam Paragon, Bangkok\n|-\n| align = \"left\"|'''KAMIKAZE K Fight Concert '''\n| \nOctober 13, 2013\n|\nRoyal Paragon Hall, Siam Paragon, Bangkok\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Timethai}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.ilovekamikaze.com}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Thai male singers]]\n[[Category:Thai pop singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=June 2012}}\n{{Infobox musical artist \n| name           = Dharmthai Plangsilp\n| image          = Timethai 1.jpg\n| caption        =\n| background     = solo_singer\n| birth_name     = Dharmthai Plangsilp\n| alias          = Timethai\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1996|1|02}}\n| origin         = {{flagicon|Thailand}} [[Bangkok]], Thailand\n| genre = Pop and [[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]\n| occupation     = Singer\n| years_active   = 2011&ndash;present\n| label           =\u0e01\u0e32\u0e21\u0e34\u0e01\u0e32\u0e40\u0e0a\u0e48 [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]] \u0e40\u0e22\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e34\u0e27\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e01 [[Yes!Music]]\n| website        = https://www.facebook.com/timethaiofficialpage\n}}\n\n'''Dharmthai Plangsilp''' ({{lang-th|\u0e18\u0e32\u0e21\u0e44\u0e17 \u0e41\u0e1e\u0e25\u0e07\u0e28\u0e34\u0e25\u0e1b\u0e4c}} - {{IPA-th|t\u02b0\u0251\u02d0mt\u02b0a\u026a p\u02b0l\u00e6\u014bs\u026an}}) (born January 2, 1996), known professionally as '''Timethai''' ({{IPA-th|t\u02b0\u0251\u02d0mt\u02b0a\u026a}}), is a Thai singer, songwriter, and dancer.  Timethai was discovered in 2010 when [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]]'s casting staff came across Timethai's Youtube videos which have been uploaded by a channel named 'Dharmthai'.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/user/dharmthai Dharmthai channel on Youtube ]</ref>  Timethai's dancing and choreography skills, cultivated since he was 7 years old, which couple uniquely with his ability to play traditional Thai instruments such as the Thai alto xylophone, Thai alto bamboo xylophone and Kong Wong ({{lang-th|\u0e06\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e27\u0e07}}),<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UaV2WHeKQYo &#91;Scoop&#93; Timethai Timeline]</ref> captured the attention of the casting staff, who offered Timethai a one-year singing and dancing training opportunity, and soon signed him to their label [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]] under RS PLC. He graduated with a bachelor's degree from Srinakarinwirot University.\n\nTimethai's debut single, \"No More\", featuring Tomo and his unique hip-hop dancing style, was released in December 2011.  The music video \"No More\"<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N__KiLe4vhQ No More music video]</ref> reached more than 10,000,000 views on Youtube within just 5 months<ref>[http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1039 \u201c\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e25\u0e30 (No More)\u201d \u0e41\u0e23\u0e07\u0e17\u0e30\u0e25\u0e38 10,000,000 view \u0e41\u0e25\u0e49\u0e27\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32!! ] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006074009/http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1039 |date=2012-10-06 }}</ref> and have been discussed nationwide.  Timethai followed up the release of his debut single with his second single \"The End\"<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=viD2tvNzhdQ The End music video]</ref> in April 2012. One month after its release, \"The End\" charted at number one in Thailand.<ref>[http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1027 Timethai \u0e41\u0e23\u0e07\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e22\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07 \u201c..\u0e08\u0e1a\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22 (The End)\u201d \u0e1e\u0e38\u0e48\u0e07\u0e02\u0e36\u0e49\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e48\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e15\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e19\u0e14\u0e31\u0e1a 1 \u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006104655/http://ilovekamikaze.com/news/details/1027 |date=2012-10-06 }}</ref> Timethai is considered to be a rising newcomer in Thailand's music industry as well as Thailand's most popular young solo male artist.\n\n==Singles==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Singles\n!Album\n|-\n| rowspan = \"1\"|2011\n|No More (\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e25\u0e30) Feat. Tomo [[K-Otic]] \n| rowspan = \"4\"|TIMETHAI \n|-\n| rowspan = \"3\"|2012\n|The End (\u0e08\u0e1a\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22)\n|-\n|Top Secret (\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e30\u0e44\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e25\u0e37\u0e21\u0e1a\u0e2d\u0e01)\n|-\n|Always Da One (\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d) \n|-\n| rowspan = \"4\"|2013\n|In Time (\u0e21\u0e32\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e08\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e30) \n| rowspan = \"5\"|DRIFE \n|-\n|Blame It On Me (\u0e40\u0e08\u0e47\u0e1a\u0e04\u0e19\u0e40\u0e14\u0e35\u0e22\u0e27\u0e01\u0e47\u0e1e\u0e2d)\n|-\n|Spy (\u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e31\u0e19\u0e18\u0e38\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e49\u0e2d)\n|-\n|All l Need (\u0e41\u0e04\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e40\u0e18\u0e2d)\n|-\n| rowspan = \"1\"|2014\n|Hidden Line (\u0e0a\u0e39\u0e49\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e44\u0e25\u0e19\u0e4c) Feat. \u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e41\u0e15 \u0e2d\u0e32\u0e23\u0e4c\u0e2a\u0e22\u0e32\u0e21\n|-\n| rowspan = \"1\"|2017\n|Don't Judge Me\n|-\n| rowspan = \"2\"|2018\n|Feelin with Twopee Southside and Notep\n|-\n|It's Time Feat. \u0e2b\u0e27\u0e32\u0e22\n|-\n| rowspan = \"2\"|2019\n|Impossible\n|-\n|Never Know \n|-HipHop\n\n\n|}\n\n== Studio albums==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" width=\"250px\"|Album details\n!align=\"left\" width=\"300px\"|Track listing\n|-\n| align = \"left\"|''' TIMETHAI ''' \n* Released: 2012\n* Label: [[Kamikaze (record label)|Kamikaze]]\n* Formats: Mini Album\n| \n#  No More (\u0e23\u0e31\u0e01\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e44\u0e21\u0e48\u0e21\u0e35\u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01\u0e25\u0e30)\n#  The End (\u0e08\u0e1a\u0e21\u0e31\u0e49\u0e22)\n#  Top Secret (\u0e21\u0